Document: SliderJoint3D
Path: godot/classes/class_sliderjoint3D.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of SliderJoint3D related to angular and linear limits, motion, and orthogonal behavior, including damping, restitution, softness, and distance/angle limits.

The following properties can be set and retrieved using the `set_param(param: Param, value: float)` and `get_param(param: Param) -> float` methods, where `Param` is an enum value corresponding to the specific property.

Property: angular_limit/damping (float) = 0.0
The amount of damping of the rotation when the limit is surpassed. A lower damping value allows a rotation initiated by body A to travel to body B slower.

Property: angular_limit/lower_angle (float) = 0.0
The lower limit of rotation in the slider.

Property: angular_limit/restitution (float) = 0.7
The amount of restitution of the rotation when the limit is surpassed. Does not affect damping.

Property: angular_limit/softness (float) = 1.0
A factor applied to all rotation once the limit is surpassed. Makes all rotation slower when between 0 and 1.

Property: angular_limit/upper_angle (float) = 0.0
The upper limit of rotation in the slider.

Property: angular_motion/damping (float) = 1.0
The amount of damping of the rotation in the limits.

Property: angular_motion/restitution (float) = 0.7
The amount of restitution of the rotation in the limits.

Property: angular_motion/softness (float) = 1.0
A factor applied to all rotation in the limits.

Property: angular_ortho/damping (float) = 1.0
The amount of damping of the rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

Property: angular_ortho/restitution (float) = 0.7
The amount of restitution of the rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

Property: angular_ortho/softness (float) = 1.0
A factor applied to all rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

Property: linear_limit/damping (float) = 1.0
The amount of damping that happens once the limit defined by linear_limit/lower_distance and linear_limit/upper_distance is surpassed.

Property: linear_limit/lower_distance (float) = -1.0
The minimum difference between the pivot points on their X axis before damping happens.

Property: linear_limit/restitution (float) = 0.7
The amount of restitution once the limits are surpassed. The lower, the more velocity-energy gets lost.

Property: linear_limit/softness (float) = 1.0
A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis once the limits get surpassed. The lower, the slower the movement.

Property: linear_limit/upper_distance (float) = 1.0
The maximum difference between the pivot points on their X axis before damping happens.

Property: linear_motion/damping (float) = 0.0
The amount of damping inside the slider limits.

Property: linear_motion/restitution (float) = 0.7
The amount of restitution inside the slider limits.

Property: linear_motion/softness (float) = 1.0
A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis as long as the slider is in the limits. The lower, the slower the movement.

Property: linear_ortho/damping (float) = 1.0
The amount of damping when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

Property: linear_ortho/restitution (float) = 0.7
The amount of restitution when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

Property: linear_ortho/softness (float) = 1.0
A factor applied to the movement across axes orthogonal to the slider.
---CHUNK---
